<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53122b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122b">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122b"> 122(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Suddodana, Sakya Mooni, <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122b"><li>FW 60.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53122b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53122b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122b">MS BL 47476b-177</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:375 <a name="cd10" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53122b">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Le roi <mark>&Ccedil;ouddhodana</mark> r&eacute;gnait sur Kapilavastou, et il en &eacute;tait la plus noble parure. Il &eacute;tait bienveillant et lib&eacute;ral; il ignorait l&apos;orgueil et il pratiquait la justice. Il courait aux ennemis les plus braves, qui tombaient dans les batailles comme des &eacute;l&eacute;phants frapp&eacute;s par Indra. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <p>&Ccedil;ouddhodana, roi issu de la race des <mark>&Ccedil;&acirc;kyas</mark>, avait &eacute;pous&eacute; plusieurs reines.</p> <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 7f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The Buddha&apos;s father, King Suddhodana was a Kshatriya of Mongolian stock and was opposed by the Brahmans. He was of the tribe of the Sakyas and from this the Buddha is often called <i>Sakya Muni</i>, the ascetic of the Sakyas. </mm> </dd></dl>
